HEADWORD: Lactometer
<hw>Lac*tom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>lac</ets>, <ets>lactis</ets>, milk + <ets>meter</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>lactom⟦egrave⟧tre</ets>. Cf. <er>Galactometer</er>.]</ety> <def>An
instrument for estimating the purity or richness of milk, as a measuring
glass, a specific gravity bulb, or other apparatus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lactone</ent>⟦br⟧
